                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11756.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-30T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 28, 3 p.m. Please convey to Admiral Cradock the sincere thanks and
                    appreciation of this Government for the friendly interest manifested in his
                    message to you, and say it will appreciate any future assistance he may be able
                    to render along the lines indicated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
